    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-21T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/7–2049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Venezuela</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-21T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 21, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>263. Latest reports in Guat indicate fighting between followers of Arana, who was
                    Chief of Armed Forces,<note n="1" xml:id="d397fn1">Col. Francisco Arana, Chief
                        of the Guatemalan Armed Forces, had been assassinated in Guatemala on July
                        18.</note> on one hand and those of President and Minister of National
                        Defense<note n="2" xml:id="d397fn2">Lt. Col. Jacobo Arbenz Guzmán.</note> on
                    the other, ceased late Tues<note n="3" xml:id="d397fn3">July 19, 1949.</note>
                        (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 457<note n="4" xml:id="d397fn4">Not
                        printed; it requested information on the assassination and outbreak of
                        fighting in Guatemala.</note>). Good offices dipl corps instrumental
                    preventing prolongation fighting. No casualties Amer citizens reported. General
                    situation now calm.</p>
                <p>Fighting by Arana followers apparently lacking in plan and coordination and
                    probably resulted as spontaneous reaction assassination and arrest certain Arana
                    supporters. Whole incident seems instigated by Army elements allied with <gloss
                        target="#t_PAR1">PAR</gloss> and other radical groups to prevent Arana from
                    gaining full control Army fol successful election last week of additional Arana
                    supporters to Supreme War Council. <pb facs="0672" n="656" xml:id="pg_656"/>
                    Overall result appears signify defeat of moderate elements govt and substantial
                    strengthening leftists.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
